        <abstract> 
<p>CD thinks JJW’s account [in <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7137</hi>] is significant for a theory of generation and should go to some scientific society; suggests additional data is needed. Quotes cases of subsequent progeny apparently affected by a previous impregnation. Perhaps not prudent to allude to "despised" Pangenesis, which CD fully believes will have its day.</p> 
        </abstract>
